{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/healthkit"},{"type":"text","text":" provides a central repository for health and fitness data on iPhone and Apple Watch. With a quick setup, you can enable a Healthkit integration with your app, allowing Point SDK to collect data from Healthkit and upload it to Point’s database to be processed."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Healthkit stores all user data on the user’s device, so all data collection happens locally, on the device. This means that this integration is only possible in iPhone devices, as other devices don’t provide support for Healthkit."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"anchor":"Setting-Up-your-Project","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Setting Up your Project"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before you start using Point SDK, you must perform the following changes to your Xcode project settings:"}]}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Enable "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"HealthKit capabilities"}]},{"type":"text","text":" in your app."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add permissions configuration"}]}]}]},{"anchor":"Enable-HealthKit-capabilities","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Enable HealthKit capabilities"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Xcode, select the project and add the HealthKit capability."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It is highly recommended that you also enable "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Background Deli